In the sample code above, `fullName` is an alias of the `name` property. Both the `name` and `fullName` variables are `John Doe`.

You can use an underscore to name the argument which is not used in an arrow function. It makes the code more readable.

```js
// No arguments
const noop = _ => {};

const range = (min, max) => (
    Array(max - min + 1).fill(0).map((_, i) => min + i);
